            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-07-22T15:31:42+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-22T15:31:42+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-22T06:01:42Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-22T06:01:42Z">
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A trough over southern South Australia will weaken overnight, with a ridge of high pressure to build over the west of the State later. A high pressure system will slowly approach South Australia on Thursday, then move over the State on Friday and Saturday. The high is expected to move to the north of South Australia during Sunday, with a trough to build over the west of the State in the evening.</text>
                <text type="preamble">Wind and wave forecasts are averages. Wind gusts can be 40 per cent stronger than the forecast, and stronger still in squalls and thunderstorms. Maximum waves can be twice the forecast height.</text>
            </forecast-period>
